<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1231/88: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-26T18:00:00-05:00">January 26, 1934—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>10. Your No. 3, January 25, 5 p.m. Studies relating to agreement with
                            Mexico have been going on here for some time and are nearing completion.
                            I hope to be able to inform you shortly when this Government will be
                            able to proceed with the discussions with the representatives of Mexico.
                            If agreeable to the Mexican authorities it is desired that the
                            discussions take place in Washington.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>